          "field_id": "a_diagnosis_of_malignant_phyllodes_tumor_requires_at_least_10_mitoses_per_10_high_power_fields_40x_o",
          "label": "A diagnosis of malignant phyllodes tumor requires at least 10 mitoses per 10 high power fields (40x objective and 10x eyepiece) or at least 5 mitoses/mm2. Mitotic activity in benign phyllodes tumor is usually low (less than or equal to 4 mitoses per 10 HPFs or less than 2.5 mitoses per mm2). Borderline phyllodes tumors usually have 5 to 9 mitoses per 10 HPF (2.5 to 5 mitoses/mm2).1",
